  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6563.86 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6550 (-10.6B) and max positive gamma at 6600 (+4.2B), dealers are currently in buy-mode as spot trades above the massive negative gamma wall at 6550. The breakout regime with -45.3B total GEX means dealers will aggressively buy any dip toward 6550 and sell any push toward 6600, creating a tight trading range with amplified moves at the boundaries. Watch 6550 as the critical support level where dealer buying should intensify, while 6600 becomes the key resistance where dealer selling pressure kicks in.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect volatile ping-pong action between 6550 and 6600 with sharp reversals at both levels.",
